### What this means in practice

- **Before 1 January 2029:** your rights are governed by the Terms and
  Conditions above — free to use, modify, self-host and build on for any
  Permitted Purpose; the only carve-out is a Competing Use.
- **On or after 1 January 2029:** the same code is available to you under the
  Apache License, Version 2.0, with no Competing Use restriction. You may treat
  it as fully open source from that date forward.

